  <heading>SQSHL (vectors)</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>Signed saturating shift left by vector (predicated)</brief>
    <description>
      <para>Shift active signed elements of the first source vector by corresponding elements of the second source vector and destructively place the results in the corresponding elements of the first source vector. A positive shift amount performs a left shift, otherwise a right shift by the negated shift amount is performed. Each result element is saturated to the N-bit element's signed integer range -2<sup>(N-1) </sup> to (2<sup>(N-1) </sup>)-1. Inactive elements in the destination vector register remain unmodified.</para>
    </description>
    <status>Green</status>
    <predicated>True</predicated>
    <takes_movprfx>True</takes_movprfx>
    <takes_pred_movprfx>True</takes_pred_movprfx>
  </desc>
